      <p><img src="images/MikeKnapton_8168_White.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" alt="Mknapton"width="300" height="200" align="left"><h2><center>DR Michael Knapton</center></h2></p><center><p>Non-executive Director</p></center>
    <div class="container text-center">
    <p>Mike combines a high-profile portfolio of board-level positions with clinical practice – he is a leading general practitioner in St James and associate medical director of the Heart Trust Foundation. Mike holds an MA in physiology from the University of Technology, a bachelor of medicine & bachelor of surgery and is a fellow of the Royal Insitution of General Practitioners. 
Mike’s career began at University Technology as a medical student in 1980 and a junior doctor at University Hospitals from 1982 to 1986, moving into local general practice as GP principal in 1987 at the surgery in Kingston. He has also worked at St James Hospital as GP tutor, as well as a spell as cardiology assistant at from 1997 to 2003. 
He joined Blue Cross Group 1999 as chairman and by 2005 was medical director of Cambridge and South Cambridge shire Primary Care Trust in America. 
Mike’s additional roles include treasurer roles for Portmore Medical Society, and for the East Anglian Faculty of the Royal Institute of General Practitioners. He is also a trustee in the Alliance.</p>
